manifest_analysis.title:
Clear text traffic is Enabled For App
[android:usesCleartextTraffic=true]
manifest_analysis.desc: The app intends to use cleartext network traffic, such as cleartext HTTP, FTP stacks, DownloadManager, and MediaPlayer. The default value for apps that target API level 27 or lower is "true". Apps that target API level 28 or higher default to "false". The key reason for avoiding cleartext traffic is the lack of confidentiality, authenticity, and protections against tampering; a network attacker can eavesdrop on transmitted data and also modify it without being detected.
manifest_analysis.name: Clear text traffic is Enabled For App [android:usesCleartextTraffic=true]

nx.description: The shared object has NX bit set. This marks a memory page non-executable making attacker injected shellcode non-executable.

stack_canary.description: This shared object has a stack canary value added to the stack so that it will be overwritten by a stack buffer that overflows the return address. This allows detection of overflows by verifying the integrity of the canary before function return.

relocation_readonly.description: This shared object has full RELRO enabled. RELRO ensures that the GOT cannot be overwritten in vulnerable ELF binaries. In Full RELRO, the entire GOT (.got and .got.plt both) is marked as read-only.

rpath.description: The shared object does not have run-time search path or RPATH set.

runpath.description: The shared object does not have RUNPATH set.

fortify.description: The shared object does not have any fortified functions. Fortified functions provides buffer overflow checks against glibc's commons insecure functions like strcpy, gets etc. Use the compiler option -D_FORTIFY_SOURCE=2 to fortify functions.

E, por alguma razão, há 300 pessoas querendo comprar suas maçãs." },{ type: "quote", body: "A demanda é maior do que a oferta, então a lógica é que você aumente o preço até que só tenha 100 pessoas que ainda querem sua fruta." },{ type: "html", body: "Você vendeu todas as maçãs e ganhou mais dinheiro do que esperava. Dessa maneira, a oferta e demanda garantem que as taxas de câmbio estejam sempre mudando." } ] }, { title: "Quais moedas são negociadas no Forex?", content: [ { type: "html", body: "Existem as principais, cruzadas e exóticas." }, { type: "html", body: "As Principais são as moedas mais populares, elas são a maior parte do mercado. Por exemplo, EUR/GBP (Euro para Libra) ou GBP/JPY (Libra em relação ao Iene Japonês) são taxas cruzadas." },{ type: "html", body: "Nós utilizamos as cruzadas para fazer com que os cálculos sejam mais fáceis: menos trabalhoso caso você esteja negociando uma moeda que não seja o dólar com uma outra moeda que também não é dólar. A primeira é a negociação com empresas estrangeiras. Você se lembra de como funciona a demanda, né? Outros negociantes, é claro, percebem isso e entram em ação, tentando comprar essa moeda antes que a taxa dispare. Não posso fazer isso eu mesmo?", content: [ { type: "html", body: "Pessoas comuns não tem permissão para negociar diretamente no mercado Forex." },{ type: "html", body: "Você só pode negociar através de sua corretora. It is a global market where people and companies trade currencies." }, { type: "html", body: "They say, New York never sleeps. The trading continues non-stop too. The same is true for Forex." }, { type: "html", body: "The average daily trading volume is around $5 trillion - This is equal to 25% of the GDP of the USA in 2017." },{ type: "quote", body: "GDP stands for Gross Domestic Product - the total dollar value of all goods and services produced in a country during a single year." },{ type: "html", body: "Can you imagine this number? We can’t either.
The action happens on a daily basis. It is huge! " }, { type: "html", body: "The main currency used on the Forex market is the USD, so all other currencies are priced against it. This is the exchange rates." }, { type: "img", body: "https://drive.google.com/uc?authuser=0&id=1klEKuBHJ4OnOzAQi6PWdFm3EjN6ue4Oh&export=download" } ] }, { title: "Yeah, I’ve heard something about exchange rates. Gimme more!", content: [ { type: "html", body: "Exchange rates are similar to price tags in a shop. They show how much another currency costs in dollars." }, { type: "html", body: "Yup, all currencies have their short names:" }, { type: "html", body: "USD - United States Dollar ($)" }, { type: "html", body: "GBP - British Pound Sterling (£)" }, { type: "html", body: "EUR - Euro (€)" }, { type: "html", body: "Those abbreviations are used to describe currency rates. For example, GBP/USD 1.3159 means that for one pound you can buy $1.3159 USD." }, { type: "img", body: "https://drive.google.com/uc?authuser=0&id=10KH9jUR49XO0YxKw6CaVDPlf2U3PcjN5&export=download" }, { type: "html", body: "Unlike your favorite supermarket, here prices are calculated precisely up to four digits to the right of its decimal point. This is very important, because even the slightest change ($0.0001) can cause a huge loss." }, { type: "html", body: "Suppose your USD seller rounds up the price from 1.3259 to 1.3260. This means you lose $0.0001 from every pound, and if you trade £1 Billion, you’re gonna lose $100,000 USD." }, { type: "quote", body: "Dude, you can buy a BMW X6, an Audi RX or a Porsche Carrera for that money! " }, { type: "html", body: "When you trade foreign exchange, the current exchange rate applies. These change every single second of the day." } ] }, { title: "Why currency rates change so often?", content: [ { type: "html", body: "The amount of foreign currency in the world is limited unless the government decides to print more banknotes… For the sake of simplicity let’s just say that it is limited." }, { type: "html", body: "When limits apply the laws of supply and demand come into play. Very briefly, when demand rises, the price increases. " }, { type: "html", body: "Let’s say you have 100 apples. And somehow you have 300 people willing to buy your apples." },{ type: "quote", body: "The demand is higher than the supply, so it’s only logical for you to increase the price until you have only 100 people who still want your fruit." },{ type: "html", body: "You’ve sold all of the apples and earned more money than you expected. You can reinvest your profit, buy more apples and sell them again at the higher price." },{ type: "html", body: "It works exactly the same on foreign exchange markets. When sellers see the demand rising, they raise the price to sell their foreign currency and earn more profit." }, { type: "html", body: "On the other hand, if there are only 50 people who want to buy your apples, you’ll have to lower the price to sell them all. playstore_details.title: Bitcoin Trading: Investment App for Beginners
playstore_details.description:
🚀 Real Time Bitcoin trading simulator with cryptocurrency and Forex Online Rates.

Become A Professional Trader By Playing A Game! 

💎Investing game  with real life experience
💸 Free practice for beginners

Are you interested in blockchain  and cryptocurrency? Are you looking for a way to learn trading Bitcoin, Ethereum and other altcoins? Then Crypto Trading App is exactly what you need!


Bitcoin trading app is an online trading simulator with variety of functions that let you get practiced in crypto trading in a fun and risk free way.


Our crypto game  supports more than 30 crypto pairs which you can trade directly from the app. You don't require having any Bitcoin or Ethereum  wallet, everything is being done on the game. When you start playing you get $10000 to use it for playing. In other words, you get free Bitcoin and/or Ethereum to start your trading practice.

You can manage your crypto investment easily within the game. Bitcoin trading app also provides a variety of trade functions like trade & order history, several time frames, bitcoin charts and updates, etc.

You don't need to take any bitcoin trading course or read any bitcoin books. While playing you not only gain practice but also have the opportunity to read Bitcoin news and get expert advice and tips directly from the app. 

You don’t need to pass any registration or verification for playing. Our app is . completely free to download and play. Don’t forget to share your results with friends.


Our game is created by real professionals who have collected all the necessary stuff a real Forex trader needs to know in one place. You don't need to lose a lot of time reading and learning from various sources. We provide you real case-studies, stories, tips and much more. Everything that a successful trader needs to know is concentrated in a simple game. We don't waste your time with academic or theoretical facts -we help you to learn and practice the skills that are really important.


You will learn the fundamental principles of trading, test your skills, develop your knowledge. Everything is simple and fun, you have nothing to risk - yet so much to gain.


Download the app, learn to trade, stay updated about cryptocurrency news, follow expert advice and tips and become a professional trader’s;

The game is ideal for those you want to get practiced without risking a single dollar! Start your journey today.


Main features:

Educational stories, blockchain and cryptocurrency news updates, informative content.

 Virtual Trading simulator - Bitcoin, Ethereum, Ripple and more crypto currency instruments (BTC/USD, ETH/USD, etc)
 Forex trading Basics, Expert tips for beginners, Social - Copy trading Strategies: a step by step master class.


What's New
+ Added new crypto currencies
+ New Bitcoin Trading simulator
+ Added new Stories about "How to find Broker"
+ Updated Trusted Brokers table, broker’s rating recalculated

General Risk Warning: financial services carry a high risk. Investors may lose all their invested capital.
